@bl 2.5 representing instructions in the computer
@1m instruction format
@1n machine language
@1o hexadecimal
@b1 represent binary instruction as binary fields
@b2 MIPS fields
@b3 opcode
@b4 op:opcode
@b5 rs: first register source operand
@b6 rt: second register source operand
@b7 rd: register destination operand
@b8 shamt: shift amount
@b9 funt: function code
@ba selects specific variant of operation in op field
@bb good design demands good compromises
design principle 3
@bc problem: what happens when instruction needs longer fields?
@bd keep instruction size the same length, requiring different
kinds of instruction formats
@be r-type/r-format (register)
@bf I-type/I-format (immediate)
